{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3706", "repo": "rails", "body": "would it be better to just have a :method option (instead of :gist/:gin)? after all, an index can't have more than one method. \r\n\r\nthis would simplify PostgresqlAdapter#add_index, would support all index types (btree/hash/gist/gin), would allow for user-defined index methods, and make the whole thing future proof.\r\n\r\ni personally prefer :type over :method, but that could get confused w/ index_type (i.e. \"\" or \"UNIQUE\"). also the postgres docs generally call it method.", "_id": {"$oid": "523832dbbd3543c15100f925"}, "issue_id": 3706, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3057703", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3706#issuecomment-3057703", "updated_at": "2011-12-08T04:14:29Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng", "login": "jenseng", "gravatar_id": "bc66e548a86d9635d5d1542080db5665", "html_url": "https://github.com/jenseng", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/bc66e548a86d9635d5d1542080db5665?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F848ffe097e37ee8768d50dbc688e0757.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 109489, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenseng/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-12-08T04:14:29Z", "id": 3057703, "owner": "rails"}
